story.title: Fatal Consequences - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: Jo-Jo awakens, trapped in the wreckage of her car, covered in blood. The last 48 hours of her life are a blank, and the dead man beside her . . . is a total stranger.

messages.text: Jo-Jo wakes up in a hospital recovery room in the dead of night.
Feeling up to a few questions, Miss Avery?
Do I know you?
Sorry. Detective Dylan Quinn. You‚Äôve been in an accident.
Heavily bandaged and sedated, Jo-Jo struggles to grasp the situation.
What kind of accident?
We found your car at the bottom of Grange Ravine.
I don‚Äôt remember.
You‚Äôre lucky to be alive.
Thirsty‚Ä¶I‚Äôm so thirsty.
Jo-Jo reaches for a carafe on the bedside table, only to realize she‚Äôs handcuffed to the bed.
Your friend Mr. Forrester wasn‚Äôt so lucky.
Forrester?
James Lawrence Forrester, according to his license.
I don‚Äôt‚Ä¶didn‚Äôt know him.
His body was practically on top of you in the wreckage.
He died in the accident?
He died alright, but it was no accident.
He was shot.
Quinn shows Jo-Jo his badge: ‚ÄúHomicide Division.‚Äù
And YOU shot him.
What?! No!
Don‚Äôt give me that crap. You killed him.
I don‚Äôt remember‚Ä¶I don‚Äôt own a gun.
Which is it, Miss Avery ‚Äî you don‚Äôt own a gun or you don‚Äôt remember?
I‚Ä¶I don‚Äôt know!
Detective, what the hell are you doing in here?
Questioning my prime murder suspect. What does it look like?
She looks like my patient, and she‚Äôs in no condition to answer anyone‚Äôs questions.
She‚Äôs alert, and for my money, she‚Äôs guilty.
Too bad your currency‚Äôs no good here.
But‚Äî
No buts. Get out. Now!
Quinn storms out, slamming the door.
Doctor?
Nice to see you awake, Miss Avery. I‚Äôm Dr. Luther Dante.
Will I be okay?
It was touch and go, but you‚Äôre stable. No broken bones.
You had a couple nasty gashes, but I did everything I could to minimize any scarring.
Thank you, Doctor.
Do you remember anything about the crash?
No. Nothing.
There was a man in the car with you.
Detective Quinn says I killed him.
Did you?
I honestly don‚Äôt know. I have no idea who he was.
Well, don‚Äôt worry about that now.
Doctor, can‚Äôt you take these handcuffs off?
I‚Äôm sorry. I wish I could. Quinn got a court order.
I‚Äôll see about getting it vacated in the morning.
Thank you, Dr. Dante ‚Äî for everything. I‚Äôm pretty tired.
Of course. Get some rest and I‚Äôll check in later.
If the pain gets too bad, just ring for the nurse. No heroics, okay?
Yes, doctor.
Dr. Dante steps into the corridor, closing the door behind him.
Did our little bird sing?
Not a note. She says she doesn‚Äôt remember.
Is she faking?
Possibly, but she took a significant blow to the head. The amnesia could be real.
Or she‚Äôs a very good actress.
I implanted the chip in her shoulder during surgery.
Any chance she‚Äôll find it?
If she‚Äôs looking for it, maybe.
It‚Äôs not much bigger than a grain of rice, but there‚Äôs a little swelling at the injection point.
GPS working?
Already tested it. Loud and clear.
I told her she shot Forrester.
He wasn‚Äôt shot. The crash killed him.
Thought it might give me some leverage.
I noticed you were going pretty hot and heavy with that ‚Äúbad cop‚Äù routine.
Well, I figured it would help prime the pump for your ‚Äútender bedside manner.‚Äù
Maybe so, but I can tell something‚Äôs up with you. Spill it.
I guess I don‚Äôt like using her this way‚Äî
She seems like a good kid who got mixed up in some seriously bad shit.
They always do. What‚Äôs really bothering you?
Nothing.
Oh for chrissakes, man. You can‚Äôt say it?
She looks just like Claire Noble. They could be twins.
Okay, I‚Äôll grant there‚Äôs a resemblance, but‚Äî
But nothing. You loved Claire. You lost her. The sniper was a wild card.
I was supposed to protect her, damn it!
There was nothing you could have done. You were Secret Service. Not god.
Yeah.
So what have we got so far?
Forrester contracted Jo-Jo to orchestrate and record that little S&M scene with Senator Leighton.
Looks like someone really wants to knock him out of the running.
Funny how a man with such a splendid presidential pedigree is a total mutt when it comes to sex.
He wouldn‚Äôt be the first.
True.
So, Forrester hired Jo-Jo, but we still don‚Äôt know who hired Forrester.
Any candidates?
Some viable possibilities, but no one stands out.
Too bad. What‚Äôs our next move?
She‚Äôs hidden the recording somewhere close by. But she‚Äôs good‚Äî
According to her profile, she‚Äôs a surveillance whiz.
We could be looking for almost anything.
Well, Forrester didn‚Äôt have it on him. We went over every centimeter of that cadaver.
Find anything else?
No. Just the hairpiece, colored contacts, and an elaborate fake tattoo on his hand.
His own mother wouldn‚Äôt have known him.
Accounts for his meltdown at the diner.
He wanted to be remembered.
Or misremembered‚Ä¶Okay, I‚Äôll check Arlo‚Äôs.
It‚Äôs a big place.
I‚Äôll try her locker first. Maybe plant a backup tracker for insurance.
Good idea. I‚Äôll keep you posted on things here.
Quinn exits and Dante steps back into Jo-Jo‚Äôs room. The handcuffs are dangling from the bed railing.
Jo-Jo has vanished.
